You've made my week with that kind of praise, anon, thank you.

I'm still very new to the whole writing thing but if I had to give some advice on how to write longer/more descriptive lines it would be to plan out your story, write out a rough first draft and then going back and evaluating scenes that could use more descriptive words and colorful language, editing them as you go.

I find it also helps to run your final drafts through an editor to identify problems with your text before actually putting it on pastebin as well. Reading other peoples stories can also give you a good idea on how to describe certain types of scenes and what kind of words to use, but just writing about anything and getting some practice will be the best way to improve in my opinion. Again, you can take this with a grain of salt since I haven't been writing for long, but this is just stuff that's helped me out.
